The paper proposes a novel variational auto-encoder framework for Bayesian Poisson tensor factorization, which is a machine learning technique for predictive analysis on count data. The paper addresses issues related to data sparsity and imbalance in count data values. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses multi-layer perceptron networks for encoding and sharing complex update information, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
